{
  "stem": "27.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "What kept me alive, you know, I mean, that my brother was there and my younger brother was there, and I figured, you know what I mean, that somebody has to survive to tell the world what's going on because we didn't believe that the world knows it.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because we knew we lived in a civilized world that nobody go for it for no reason whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that's what kept me alive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I'll be honest with you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The problems started after Kochendorf, all right?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Same situation, the allies were advancing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They put us in a train towards Dachau.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The train, after an hour stopped because the rails were bombed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We had to get out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then there was about 3,000 of us, OK?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then the death march started, which I think we were near the city of Ulm, U-L-M.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I think, because we seen some signs, Ulm.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You know, as you walk under the freeway?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was no more kapo.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was nothing, just SS, and their job was kill as much as they can, and they did.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If you sat down, they shot you on the spot.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you fell down, tripped, let's say, shot you on the spot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anything, any minor things they got rid of you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "To remember, back Kochendorf, I just remembered one thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, when you are in the barracks, and we slept four of us on one of those-- you know the one, two story.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, one of those bunks, four of us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, after you went in, you could not go on the toilet.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You cannot get out from the garage because if you stepped out of the garage, I mean from the barracks, they shoot you on premises.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
